    {
      "id": "jshell-301-filter-map",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "//@ anchor: filter-and-map-the-workhorses\n//@ description: filter and map — the workhorses\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\n\n// --- filter and map — the workhorses ---\n// filter(Predicate) keeps elements that match the condition\n// map(Function)     transforms each element to a new value\n\nList<String> words = List.of(\"banana\", \"apple\", \"cherry\", \"blueberry\",\n                              \"apricot\", \"avocado\", \"kiwi\", \"blackberry\");\n\n// filter: keep words starting with 'b'\nList<String> bWords = words.stream()\n    .filter(w -> w.startsWith(\"b\"))\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());\nSystem.out.println(\"Words starting with 'b': \" + bWords);\n\n// map: convert each word to its length\nList<Integer> lengths = words.stream()\n    .map(String::length)                // method reference: same as w -> w.length()\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());\nSystem.out.println(\"Word lengths           : \" + lengths);\n\n// chaining filter + map + sorted\nList<String> result = words.stream()\n    .filter(w -> w.length() > 5)        // keep words longer than 5 chars\n    .map(String::toUpperCase)           // uppercase each\n    .sorted()                           // alphabetical order\n    .collect(Collectors.toList());\nSystem.out.println(\"Long words (uppercase, sorted): \" + result);\n\n// mapToInt for numeric streams (gives access to sum/average/min/max)\ndouble avgLength = words.stream()\n    .mapToInt(String::length)\n    .average()\n    .orElse(0.0);\nSystem.out.printf(\"Average word length: %.2f%n\", avgLength);",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": "filter-and-map-the-workhorses",
      "dependsOn": [],
